Super Eagles striker Odion  Ighalo  yesterday  opened his goal accounts with Al Hilal as the Saudi Arabian  champions demolished Al Jazira 6-1 in the 2021 FIFA Club World Cup. It was the biggest victory in the tournament’s history and victory gurantees Al Hilal  a semi-final slot against Chelsea. Ighalo registered  an 36th  minute equaliser for the AFC Champions League winners as they went on rampage and hammered their Asian counterparts 6-1 in the night.   SUPER EAGLES JOB: No contract yet with Peseiro, says Pinnick     Fury backs Wilder to knock out Joshua     Sporting Lagos  FC  excites  Akinwunmi    “We believe we were much the better team, so after we went 1-0 down, we started pressing, acting as a team. Everyone started getting into the game. We scored one, we scored another and we got the result we wanted,” Ighalo said. - Advertisement - Meanwhile, Al Hilal will face Chelsea on Wednesday Mohammed bin Zayed Stadium while the first semi-final between Palmeiras and Al Ahly  comes up tomorrow at the Al Nahyan Stadium on Tuesday, 8:30pm local time